The paper deals with optimization problems over a ground set, which is a common theme in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The focus is on submodular functions, which are often studied in the context of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
